in the 16th century; the surname, however, is not associated with this meaning.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hEodhusa</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eodhus</i>’. This was the name of a bardic family associated with the Maguires of Fermanagh, also Anglicized as   Oswell   or   Oswald  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hosea","meanings":["English: variant of   Hussey  . Similarity with the Old Testament prophet's name Hosea (see 3 below) is accidental.","English: in Scotland, where the name is more common, it is sometimes a variant of   Hosie  , itself a form of   Hussey  , or else a variant of   Hossack  .","African (mainly Nigeria and Tanzania): from the Biblical personal name <i>Hosea</i>. In the Old Testament, Hosea was a prophet who married a prostitute in order to illustrate Israel's unfaithfulness to God."]},{"name":"Hosie","meanings":["Scottish (northeast Scotland): variant of Irish   Hussey  ."]},{"name":"Hassey","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Hussey  ."]},{"name":"Oswell","meanings":["English: variant of   Oswald  .","Irish (Ulster): adopted as an English equivalent of Gaelic <b>Ó hEodhusa</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eodhus</i>’ (see   Hussey  )."]},{"name":"Hosey","meanings":["English: variant of   Hussey  ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":28,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":53,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":66,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First Wa